What is Bean?

Definition: In Spring, a Bean is simply an object that is managed by the Spring IoC
(Inversion of Control) container. It's entire lifecycle is managed by Spring IOC container.

How to define a Bean:

1.Using annotations:
Ex:

@Component
public class UserService { }

//Also
@Service
public class UserService { }

2.Earlier days , we defined using xml:
<bean id="userService" class="com.example.UserService"/>

